The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business
 Tuesday, March 23, 2004  Business Briefs																								 Mumbai, March 22: The Reserve Bank has issued guidelines for formulating the best practices code to prevent frauds in a bid to ensure uniformity in content and coverage. The RBI has observed that there was no uniformity in the content and coverage of the codes prepared by some banks and documents were not prepared as envisaged by the Mitra committee (on legal aspects of bank frauds).																								 Mumbai, March 22: Indian Airlines today announced a drastic cut in fares  of over 60 per cent in some routes  for its passengers travelling on the domestic leg before the flight proceeds to an international destination. The cut would be effective from April 1.																								 New Delhi, March 22: Backed by impressive growth in corporate earnings, direct tax collections surged 25.4 per cent at Rs 78,243 crore till March 15. While corporate tax collections rose 37.3 per cent to Rs 44,140 crore, income tax picked up by 12.8 per cent to Rs 34,103 crore.																								 Hyderabad, March 22: Dr Reddys Laboratories (DRL) has filed an abbreviated new drug application with the United States Food and Drug Administration (USFDA) for 250, 500 and 750 mg levetiracetam tablets.																								 New Delhi, March 22: PowerGrid plans to establish a cross-country grid by 2009 at a cost of Rs 75,000 crore to carry power to deficit states. We are trying to advance the creation of national grid by 2009. The money will be investment in the next 10 years, said chairman and managing director R. P. Singh.
